article.headline: Tennessee-Martin takes down Eastern Illinois 87-84 in OT
article.linkText: Tennessee-Martin takes down Eastern Illinois 87-84 in OT
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Twymond Howard scored a career-high 29 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Myles Taylor scored 23 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Tennessee-Martin past Eastern Illinois in overtime Thursday night. Taylor-for the second time in his career-shot 13 for 14 from the free-throw line. The Skyhawks, currently the hottest team in the Ohio Valley Conference, won its sixth straight. Demetrius McReynolds hit a 3 with 3:52 left in overtime to give the Panthers their only lead in the extra period at 76-75. Taylor made two free throws and Jalen Variste's jumper made it 79-76 with 2:34 to play. The game was knotted at 73 at the end of regulation. Terrence Durham chipped in 13 points for Tennessee-Martin (16-12, 8-5). McReynolds and Trae Anderson each scored 19 points for Eastern Illinois (11-16, 7-7), which lost its third straight.
